<TITLE> FAO rep awarded for contribution to development </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 12 (bdnews24.com)FAO representative in Bangladesh Ad Spijkers has been awarded the Kobi Abu Zafar Obaidullah Award 2009 for his outstanding contribution to agricultural development in Bangladesh. "There are massive challenges for us here, including that of the huge population," said Spijkers as he accepted the award last week. Industries minister Dilip Barua attended the ceremony as chief guest and information secretary Mr. A T M Fazlul Karim as special guest The FAO representative welcomed the present government's priority on agriculture at the forefront of the development efforts. Spijkers, who moved to Bangladesh in 2006 and since faced a string of challenges including Cyclone Sidr, floods and outbreaks of avian flu, hoped Bangladesh would progress to being a prosperous country over the next decade. The award ceremony was held by the Kobi Abu Zafar Obaidullah Foundation at the Kobi Sufia Kamal Auditorium of the National Museum last Sunday. Spijkers said Abu Zafar Obaidullah was not only a poet but also a great man and well known personality in the UN as well as in many other forums. He recalled his working relationship with Obaidullah from as long as twenty years ago in China and Cambodia. The FAO representative also remembered Obaidullah's very significant contribution to "culture and agriculture" and hoped he would always be remembered.
